<task id="057" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6">
  <metadata>
    <title>D-C-08 + D-C-09 + D-C-10 — User affordances: "Send to Workspace" + "Add to Assistant" + "Pin to Matter"</title>
    <status>pending</status>
    <estimated-effort>1.5 days</estimated-effort>
    <phase>Phase C — Tri-directional Workspace (Pillar 6b)</phase>
    <wave>C-G2 (parallel after 6a)</wave>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>054, 055, 056 (chat tools that affordances invoke)</dependencies>
    <tags>frontend, react, fluent-ui, ai-widgets, workspace</tags>
    <rigor-level>FULL</rigor-level>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Three new affordances modifying workspace state; spans multiple SpaarkeAi components; UX-critical (visible to end user).</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>C-G2</parallel-group>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Build three user affordances per spec FR-39:
    1. **"Send to Workspace" button** on chat assistant messages — promotes chat message
       content to a new workspace tab via direct workspace state API call (or via chat
       tool invocation if simpler); default `visibleToAssistant: false` (user-initiated).
    2. **"Add to Assistant" toggle** on user-created tabs — flips `visibleToAssistant`
       from false → true; updates tab via `WorkspaceStateService` directly (this is a
       user action, not a chat tool).
    3. **"Pin to Matter" affordance** — calls `WorkspaceStateService.PinTabAsync(matterId)`
       which promotes the tab to Cosmos durable storage attached to matter record.
    All components use Fluent v9 per ADR-012. Components live in
    `@spaarke/ai-widgets` shared library; consumed by SpaarkeAi shell. Dark-mode parity
    verified per ADR-021. Each affordance emits the appropriate `workspace.*` PaneEventBus
    event so other panes (e.g., trace widget from task 061) observe the change.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior React/Fluent-v9 engineer with deep familiarity with SpaarkeAi shell + workspace
    tab manager + PaneEventBus contract.
  </role>

  <goal>
    All three affordances visible + functional in SpaarkeAi shell. Persistence verified
    via reload (pinned tabs reappear from Cosmos). PaneEventBus events emitted. Dark-mode
    parity verified. Fluent v9 component conventions followed.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="project-spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-plan">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/plan.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="root-claude">CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="workspace-arch">docs/architecture/SPAARKEAI-WORKSPACE-ARCHITECTURE.md</file>
    <file purpose="component-model">docs/architecture/SPAARKEAI-COMPONENT-MODEL.md</file>
    <file purpose="dashboard-widget-model">docs/architecture/SPAARKEAI-DASHBOARD-AND-WIDGET-MODEL.md</file>
    <file purpose="workspace-tab">src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/types/WorkspaceTab.ts</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-012">Fluent v9 component patterns; shared lib `@spaarke/ai-widgets`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Dark-mode parity verified for every new component.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-030">PaneEventBus 4 channels; additive event types only on `workspace` channel.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-39">All three affordances functional + persisted via state service.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project R6 Pillar 6b">"Add to Assistant" is the user override that flips `visibleToAssistant: true` for tabs that default false (user-created).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project R6">No new PCF; consume existing SpaarkeAi shell + workspace tab manager. Components live in shared lib per ADR-012.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <topic>frontend/fluent-v9-affordances</topic>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/patterns/ui/fluent-v9-component-authoring.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/ui/fluent-v9-theming.md</file>
      <file>.claude/skills/fluent-v9-component/SKILL.md</file>
      <file>docs/architecture/SPAARKEAI-WORKSPACE-ARCHITECTURE.md</file>
      <file>docs/architecture/SPAARKEAI-COMPONENT-MODEL.md</file>
      <file>docs/architecture/SPAARKEAI-DASHBOARD-AND-WIDGET-MODEL.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-012-shared-components.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-030-pane-event-bus.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context Check + Rigor Declaration">"🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: FULL — 3 affordances; UX-critical; Fluent v9 + dark-mode + persistence."</step>
    <step order="1" name="Review Progress">Read TASK-INDEX; confirm 054/055/056 complete; chat tools available.</step>
    <step order="2" name="Gather Resources">Read SpaarkeAi shell + chat message component + workspace tab manager + Fluent v9 author pattern.</step>
    <step order="3" name="Build SendToWorkspaceButton">In `@spaarke/ai-widgets`; appears on chat assistant messages; clicking creates tab; user-initiated → `visibleToAssistant: false`.</step>
    <step order="4" name="Build AddToAssistantToggle">In `@spaarke/ai-widgets`; toggle in tab header; flips visibility flag; calls state service.</step>
    <step order="5" name="Build PinToMatterAffordance">In `@spaarke/ai-widgets`; calls `WorkspaceStateService.PinTabAsync(matterId)` via BFF; promotes to Cosmos.</step>
    <step order="6" name="Integrate into Shell">Wire into SpaarkeAi shell; verify rendering order + dark-mode parity.</step>
    <step order="7" name="Persistence Test">Reload session; verify pinned tabs reappear from Cosmos; non-pinned tabs cleared from Redis after 24h TTL.</step>
    <step order="8" name="UI Tests">Per ui-test skill: render each component in light + dark; click handlers fire correct events.</step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality Gates (FULL)">code-review + adr-check (ADR-012/021/030).</step>
    <step order="10" name="Document + Complete">TASK-INDEX 057 ✅.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="npm">Build + type-check + lint</tool>
    <tool name="git">Stage + commit</tool>
    <tool name="fluent-v9-component">Skill for Fluent v9 component authoring conventions</tool>
    <tool name="ui-test">Skill for browser-based UI verification</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/components/affordances/SendToWorkspaceButton.tsx (NEW)</output>
    <output type="code">src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/components/affordances/AddToAssistantToggle.tsx (NEW)</output>
    <output type="code">src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/components/affordances/PinToMatterButton.tsx (NEW)</output>
    <output type="code">SpaarkeAi shell integration points (chat message, tab header)</output>
